          {
            "level": 4,
            "text": "How do we decide where to build boreholes?"
          }
        ],
        "paragraphs": [
          "Support our mission by contributing a donation.",
          "Why give?",
          "Your donation helps fund borehole projects that deliver safe, drinkable water to underserved communities in Nigeria.",
          "100% of donations go toward water infrastructure, maintenance, and sustainability efforts, ensuring every dollar creates real change.",
          "We don’t just build boreholes—we implement long-term water solutions, empowering local communities to maintain and manage their resources.",
          "We provide regular updates, project reports, and impact stories, so you see exactly how your support is making a difference.",
          "As a 501(c)(3) nonprofit, all donations are tax-deductible, making your generosity even more rewarding.",
          "Every donation, big or small, is a step closer in transforming lives through clean water!",
          "It all begins with a mission. Maybe you want to make a difference. Maybe you believe that access to clean water should be a human right, not a privilege. Or maybe you see the impact that safe drinking water can have on health, education, and entire communities.",
          "Whatever drives you, the Nigeria Water Project is here to turn that vision into reality. Through sustainable borehole projects, we’re bringing clean water to underserved villages in Nigeria—and your support makes all the difference.",
          "Nigeria Water Project is under Mud Global Solutions a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, which means your donation is tax-deductible. After donating, you will receive a donation receipt with our EIN (Employer Identification Number: 33-3795843), which you can use when filing your taxes. If you donate more than $250, we will provide a written acknowledgment as required by the IRS. Please consult a tax professional to ensure proper deduction based on your specific situation.",
          "100% of your donation goes directly toward building boreholes, maintaining water infrastructure, and supporting sustainable clean water initiatives in underserved Nigerian communities. We prioritize transparency, and regular project updates are shared so you can see the direct impact of your contribution",
          "Yes! Recurring donations are one of the best ways to ensure ongoing clean water access for communities. You can set up a monthly or annual donation on this website in the donation tab to make a lasting impact.",
          "We work with local communities, experts, and leaders to identify villages in urgent need of clean water. Our next project is in Ebue-Nneki, Nigeria, where access to safe drinking water is scarce. Each borehole site is chosen based on population needs, water accessibility, and long-term sustainability."
        ],
        "buttonLabels": [
          "Donate"
        ],
        "scrollingText": [
          "Why give?",
          "Your donation helps fund borehole projects that deliver safe, drinkable water to underserved communities in Nigeria.",
          "100% of donations go toward water infrastructure, maintenance, and sustainability efforts, ensuring every dollar creates real change.",
          "We don't just build boreholes—we implement long-term water solutions, empowering local communities to maintain and manage their resources.",
          "We provide regular updates, project reports, and impact stories, so you see exactly how your support is making a difference.",
          "As a 501(c)(3) nonprofit, all donations are tax-deductible, making your generosity even more rewarding.",
          "Every donation, big or small, is a step closer in transforming lives through clean water!"
        ],
        "faqs": [
          {
            "question": "How can I write off my donation in my taxes?",
            "answer": "Nigeria Water Project is under Mud Global Solutions a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization, which means your donation is tax-deductible. After donating, you will receive a donation receipt with our EIN (Employer Identification Number: 33-3795843), which you can use when filing your taxes. If you donate more than $250, we will provide a written acknowledgment as required by the IRS. Please consult a tax professional to ensure proper deduction based on your specific situation."
          },
          {
            "question": "How will my donation be used?",
            "answer": "100% of your donation goes directly toward building boreholes, maintaining water infrastructure, and supporting sustainable clean water initiatives in underserved Nigerian communities. We prioritize transparency, and regular project updates are shared so you can see the direct impact of your contribution"
          },
          {
            "question": "Can I make recurring donations?",
            "answer": "Yes! Recurring donations are one of the best ways to ensure ongoing clean water access for communities. You can set up a monthly or annual donation on this website in the donation tab to make a lasting impact."
          },
          {
            "question": "How do we decide where to build boreholes?",
            "answer": "We work with local communities, experts, and leaders to identify villages in urgent need of clean water. Our next project is in Ebue-Nneki, Nigeria, where access to safe drinking water is scarce. Each borehole site is chosen based on population needs, water accessibility, and long-term sustainability."
